Dr. Jill Biden visited Fort Drum, NY and expressed her gratitude and support for the military and their families. She shared her personal connection to the military as the daughter of a World War II veteran and the mother of a Major who served in Iraq. Dr. Biden emphasized the importance of ensuring that military service is a dignified opportunity for both service members and their families. She mentioned her White House initiative, Joining Forces, which aims to provide resources and support for military and veteran families, caregivers, and survivors. Dr. Biden concluded by expressing her hope for strong friendships, understanding of the sacrifices made by the military, and a nation that honors their service.